<Date>1544768859974</Date>< review>
I have been renting from NorCal Jump for the past 3 years and never had any issues. As soon as i request a jumper I get a call back within 10 minutes, even at 8pm, which was a shock to me the first time. I didn't answer so I received a text and we we're able to easily communicate that way.
They are always on time or even early which is a plus. Pick up is later than scheduled and the kids and adults enjoy the most out of it.
I've never experienced any hassles about location of placement of the jumpers (I've heard of other companies having so many restrictions).
The prices are reasonable for the service and time you get. I will continue to do business with them and recommend any families out there to give them a try.</review>

<text>For new and old customers, make sure to check your insurance coverage with them before any service!! Even if you have been going to them for years.

We have been taking our two children here for many years and have loved the in-office experience!

However, we will be taking our children to another dentist because unfortunately they are no longer ‚Äúin network‚Äù for our insurance (Delta Dental).

I am rating them a 3/5 not for this change, which seems to be out of their control, but for how they handled this change, specifically how they billed us for the ‚Äúdifference‚Äù between what insurance pays and what they want for payment.

Some time last year my dental plan Delta, decided they were no longer in their preferred network. So with no one telling us of this change, we went about with our normal appointment (cleaning, xrays, etc..), and come to find out many months later that they want to bill us for the amount the insurance did not pay.

My wife called months ago to clarify why this is happening and that its not appropriate to charge above what insurance has covered. She was told not to worry about it and to ignore the bill. Now, some more months later, I receive another bill for the same visit.

Because of this review (now edited because the issue is resolved), they contacted her again to assure her not to worry about the bill they sent to us.  Personally, I think this is a bad business practice to continue to send these bills to the client even though you are supposedly ‚Äúworking with the insurance company to resolve YOUR ISSUE‚Äù. Also, they encouraged my wife to contact the insurance company herself to possibly expedite the dentist offices payment! It is not our job to fight insurance companies for you to get your money! Again, this shouldn‚Äôt be the worry of the parents and you should have left us out of it!

Needless to say, we will be taking our kids elsewhere for insurance and business practice reasons.< /text><pics>None< /pics><Response>None< /Response><GmapID>0x809ade1851e57369:0x24bb705562f11768< /GmapID></record>

< text>
Check with them to make sure your insurance is still accepted here! We showed up today with our 5 kids for them to tell us they no longer accept our insurance at the reception desk. We were ready to walk out because we didn't want to pay the extra patient portion of $427. I understand if you want to change which insurance you accept, but you should let us know before we mask up in 104 degree heat. The receptionist explained the issue with the insurance in a very confusing way, which sounded at first like the insurance would cover it, until we questioned them further.

They ended up covering the patient portion, but it still kind of felt like a bait and switch.

It's really sad, because we've had such a great experience here until today, but they have really lost our trust.</text>

<Text>This pediatric dentistry is just AMAZING!!! My daughter has special needs. She is 9 years old. ALTA California recommended this dentistry.  I didn't get my hopes to high at first, just because we have had bad experiences in the past, with other dentistries.
Our first appointment was amazing. The staff is very welcoming. The waiting area is very clean. I was juggling with my daughter,  18month son, a tablet,  1st time paperwork and backpack. When the dentist assistant called us in. It was so fast we were in the waiting room for about 5mins. I was expecting a longer wait time like all the other places we've been too. She noticed I was juggling, so she just grab my daughter's hand and took her straight to the dentist tables. She explained to my daughter the areas she was allowed to play in and showed her the table where she would be laying on and equipment.  She basically gave her an overview of everything.  By the time I got to back with my son. My little girl was playing in the 2nd kids play area. Yes! There is a play area where they get seen. It was so cool! She was allowed to play to relax until she had to lay on the table. In the section she was placed in there was a toy area and window bench. So my son was busy away playing.  While I was just finishing the paperwork without being overwhelmed. The assistant called my little girl to do her Xrays. I thought I would have to go with her. Since she has had many problems with sitting still and behaviors.  The assistant actual told me it's okay, she will be fine to handle it. So she whisked her away. Came back minutes later and congratulated my daughter for taking all her Xrays with out a hitch. I actually got teary eyed, because this was the first time she was able to get all her Xrays without a tantrum. Mind you I'm still doing paperwork,  the assistant started on her teeth cleaning. Dentist came in assessed her, the dentist was so patient with my girl. Explained everything he was doing, aswell as the assistant so my girl could be as comfortable and happy as possible.  She did have a hard time with the dentist was there fo just a moment.  However, they hot her right back on the table and calmed her down. When it was all done. The assistant took me back to the secretaries at which point my kids booked to the the main kids play area. I was so flustered for a second. Cuz how do I go set up my next appointment and my kids with out supervision in the play area. Well like I said a second only. Because the assistant said quickly, no worries you can go make the appointment, I will watch the kids. Made the appointment for next visit went to my kids thanked the assistant for helping me. We left.
I cannot tell you how I loved my experienced. I was amazed and I felt welcomed my kids felt welcomed. It was the best office visit of all time. JK! Cuz we went to our second appointment today. Let me tell you it was more amazing today than the first time. I'm just in aww at the dedication all the staff have with the children and their families.  Thank you so very much, Weideman Pediatrics and Staff.< /Text>< resp>

<user>115726121947187182326<//user><user_name>Nileshni< /user_name><Date>1558763823918<//Date><rating>5<//rating>< text>
My son's first time seeing any dentist and I have to say I was very impressed from the beginning to the end. It was very easy to schedule an appointment for my son who was a new patient and upon arrival I was immediately drawn in by the beautiful decor and friendly waiting area for kids! It did not look like a regular dentist office (boring and dull) it was kid friendly. The staff were pleasant and very professional and worked well with my son. I appreciated that they took the time to read his likes and interests and incorporated that into helping him feel at ease. He was not apprehensive at all and that was because the staff were all so positive and very calm with him. I know that some people who are in any medical profession and work with children don't always have patience and in this dentist office that was not the case. They make your child feel welcomed and do everything to make sure he or she is comfortable, there was no pressure into doing anything we didn't want done. We had a follow up appointment today where they did a root canal and one of the techs was a bit more on the serious side where it seemed she was a bit annoyed with our decision to wait on the nitrous oxide, we wanted to attempt the procedure without it and let them know that if he needs it then yes will will definitely use that. Long story short once the tech started to show our son the different tools that will be used he became a bit nervous and at that time we decided to go ahead with the laughing gas. He did an amazing job and did not fidget at all during the process. I did appreciate that we were in a private room and were able to watch the procedure happen and were able to be close to our son. The doctor was very good and he was comfortable with her and the assistants. We recieved post procedure instructions and my son was given some fun goodies for doing so well.
I truly did not think that the office could be as good as people were saying but they proved me wrong. I am happy we picked Weidman pediatric dentist as our son's dental office and Dr. Andrea as his dentist. I appreciated the overall quality and professionalism from the front desk, assistants and doctor! We would recommend this place for anyone who is looking for a children's dentist! Their focus is your child and their dental health! 5 stars! ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê</text>

< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< review>
This place is a dream dentist office.

I searched heavily for a great dentist for my daughter (2 years old). I had noticed some markings on her front teeth and they were growing in uneven. I originally went to a dentist that was recommended to me in Chico. He told me she would have to have 7 crowns and it would have to be done ASAP to save the teeth. I was shocked... I didn't know her teeth had gotten this bad. I was so ashamed and sad that I let this happen to my child. I don't give her juice or sugary treats, so I was astounded she had such a bad problem. I was raised in a family with doctors so I naturally sought out a second opinion (in Reno) then a third opinion (Sacramento). The 2 other doctors told me she would have to have her four front teeth extracted and metal crowns put on the back top 2 teeth. I was just not happy with the way any 3 doctors I went to treated the situation. This is my child, she is special to me and not just another patient/paycheck.

I had a friend from The Cameron heights area highly recommended Weidmen Pediatrics. I called and spoke with the office to make an appointment. Right away I was impressed with the staff over the phone. The day of my daughters first appointment we saw Dr. Chris Lee. I LOVE him, he is so great with children. His patience and compassion is amazing. After he assessed her situation, he said he thinks there is a possibility of saving the front teeth and just doing some fillings in the back. He then answered many of my questions and educated me on why this happens to many babies/toddlers.

That day I scheduled her surgery.

The day of her surgery with Dr. Jeff Sue I was apprehensive that they were going to be able to save her teeth. I was nervous because my little girl was going to be put under Anesthesia.  I kept picturing afterwards an empty smile.
Dr. Sue walked out and informed me he was able to save all four front teeth with crowns! I instantly cried and hugged him. He is an amazing Doctor and the best I've ever seen. I wish he saw Adult patients lol!

My daughter is so important to me, I am so happy I found this place. It's truly different than any other pediatric dentist around. Not just around the Sacramento area but anywhere. Everything has gone so smoothly here, my daughter enjoys the dentist. She even says "Mom I want to see the dentist."

I can't say enough about this office, their staff, and their top notch doctors.</review>

< Text>
This place is wedged in beside the 99 Cent Store.  The prices are comparable to Super Cuts and Clipper Cuts. < Review>
A friend took me here after picking me up from the airport. Oakland is kind of hit and miss and this is definitely in a gentrifying area.The wait staff tried to hang my laptop bag, which was really kind, since it was sitting on the ground next to my chair.My companion had an entree and I opted for the plantain rellenos and the smoky chicken soup (which has a good kick to it!). Everything was great. We had one of the desserts (which I can't find online), but it was delicious.A bit on the pricier side, but a great experience all around. I'd definitely come back and explore more of the menu.<//Review>

< Review>
I got the esquite ($2), which is corn in a bowl with mayo, butter, chili powder, and a Parmesan-like cheese. Don't knock it til you've tried it cause it is delicious. The corn was cooked just right, and had a nice pop when you ate it. My complaint is that he showed up more than 30 min late to open the stand, and the line took over an hour to get through. I would recommend trying this place, but only if you have the time and patience.<//Review>

<userid>103950114571327236088< /userid><user_name>David Calvillo<//user_name><Time>1578888032946</Time><Rate>5< /Rate>< Text>
I like the vibe here. Popcorn was fresh, and drink icy cold. I do miss old school style nachos at movie theater nowadays. Theater was comfortable, and although seats did not recline in auditorium 1, seats can accommodate posteriors of the particularly wide variety.....and let's be real here...with the amount of popcorn we audience members were eating, I wouldn't be surprised if the seating were replaced in the near future. Make them even wider, sturdier, and reclinable. Who could resist the all you can eat popcorn. I sat two rows from the back, which seemed to be the perfect spot to view the screen. The three rows toward the front of the screen were a bit too close where you would have to look up so I don't recommend those seats. You might end up with a crick in your neck. Nice movie complex. I enjoyed my visit.<//Text>

<username>Parker Jennings< /username><Date>1583193474596<//Date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
<Text>I'm biased because this is my childhood movie theater and it is a wonderful staple of West Covina. It's larger than life, grandiose and beautiful architecture is really a privilege to take in. Some (and I do say some) of the theaters in here are top-notch. Expect great sound quality for the latest releases.

However, the theater does suffer from some of the most insidiously uncomfortable chairs that you can expect from a (now discount) movie theater. With a dedicated refresher package expense this theater can evolve into a much more elegant experience (think recliner lazy boy chairs or an IMAX theater).

Oh well, it's only love from me to here anyway. God bless West Covina<//Text>< pictures>

< review>
First time we bought the burger box and chicken tenders. Very good. Fresh, hot and not greasy. Price about the same as burger joints and they offer choices of dipping sauce for the tenders. We would buy them again if we happen to be hungry some other time we go. The theater is always clean so that is another plus. There is street and parking structure parking available. Handicap parking is not as close as some places but available.</review>

< Text>
I love that they have kept they're prices affordable. But I'm not super in love with the whole assigned seating thing. Most theaters that have assigned seating have big reclining chairs and waiters that bring you your food and drinks. This one does not. You also cannot pick a seat that has one gap between you and another seat holder. So basically you more than likely will end up sitting right next to someone you don't know which isn't a problem except the seats are small so you do kinda feel squished . I went to see a movie alone just because I had a chance to and although when I booked the ticket I was the only one in the row, it did not stay that way. Which is perfectly fine but I was surrounded on both sides so it felt a little uncomfortable. Aside from that its wonderful and has a great price point.< /Text>

Great movie theater very well localized with plenty of parking across the street from the West Covina Mall.

Of course the concession stand items are expensive but for the past 3 months since October 2017 they have been charging $6.35 for any show any day of course 3D is extra.

< Text>
Edwards West Covina can be a hectic experience. The ticket lines are not organized into a single waiting line, so buying your ticket is like finding the shortest line at the grocery store.  Sometimes you're lucky, sometimes you're not.  Inside the folks are friendly. Concessions are about the same price as other theaters. BUT, they recently changed to discounted pricing every day. At $6.75 for standard showings, t's the local movie bargain. Even their 3D show are "only" $10.25. Better tthan any other theater around.< /Text>

It's a movie theater.  You pay money, enter, buy snacks if you feel so inclined and watch a movie.  It's not the best theater in the world but far from the worst.  I have been coming here since it opened many years ago and never had a horror story.  Sometimes you get loud people in the theater with you, but Edwards staff will handle it if you complain.  There are also arcade games if you have time to kill.  I wouldn't do the "win a free motorcycle!" Kiosk thing they have set up in the lobby because you probably won't win.  You will, however, be contacted in a few weeks by a salesman pushing timeshares or some bs because the information you provide in the kiosk goes to marketers.< /review>

<user_id>105239018934693902357< /user_id><name>Brandon Santillan<//name>< time>
1523687118019< /time>
<Rating>4<//Rating>< text>
It's a movie theater.  You pay money, enter, buy snacks if you feel so inclined and watch a movie.  It's not the best theater in the world but far from the worst.  I have been coming here since it opened many years ago and never had a horror story.  Sometimes you get loud people in the theater with you, but Edwards staff will handle it if you complain.  There are also arcade games if you have time to kill.  I wouldn't do the "win a free motorcycle!" Kiosk thing they have set up in the lobby because you probably won't win.  You will, however, be contacted in a few weeks by a salesman pushing timeshares or some bs because the information you provide in the kiosk goes to marketers.</text>

Very good place to go to the movies with the kids. I feel very safe here, the prices are great, on sunday it's $6.50, that is just awesome. Of course it's packed crazy tight and there's no guarantee you get to see the movie you want at the time you want, but that's why you prepare and show up at least an hr early. Doable even with small children, I have a 5,9,11,13 year olds and we make it work. The theatre is not always super clean, but the amount of people they have in there working tries to make it clean really quick.

They DO check your purse when you come in, if you have nothing to hide, you should NOT have a problem. They even checked my 13 year olds purse and my 9 year old little backpack. That's fine, for the safety of the theatre and guests, I'm fine!< /review>
